cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with visual segmentation, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning a latent task representation from few pixel supervision, which is a machine learning approach (cs.LG). The authors also mention the use of reinforcement learning for interactive segmentation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also includes results for real-time interactive video segmentation, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the authors mention the use of their approach for semantic segmentation across scenes, which could be relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
